\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you tell me your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Adam Robertson Aird.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 5 Ashleigh Grove, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Benton{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Newcastle{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Tyne{\*\xmlclose} 12.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 And you're married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes. Very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You've just been married once have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes. Oh no, twice, this is second wife, my wife - my first wife died over thirty years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you tell me the dates of your two marriages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 First marriage was in 1927. 26th of December. And the second was 1948. In March the - 24th.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 1893. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname date}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Year}{\xmlattrvalue 1893}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Day
}{\xmlattrvalue 14}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Month}{\xmlattrvalue 4}}}April the 14th 1893{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Berwick on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Tweed{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Which is just about in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Northern England{\*\xmlclose}, aye. Northumberland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 One.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Only one year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where did you move to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Tweedmouth. For four years. Somewhere roughly - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 And from Tweedmouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 To Newsholme, near Blythe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 That was from the age of five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 1890 - 1902 when we came from - Newsholme to Acle near Wooler. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 1902 we }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 shifted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  from Tweedmouth -
 from - not Tweedmouth - from Newsholme to Wooler, near Wooler. And we were there from 1902 to 1914. And by then I was twenty-one. Then we shifted up to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Newcastle{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} and been here ever since. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your parents ever tell you why you moved from Berwick to Tweedmouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh it was - me father, his - his better occupation all the time. Different job, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 From Tweedmouth to Newsholme?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 To }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Newsholme}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
, that was again on the railway you see. We removed from there to-Newsholme. And the same thing happened when they moved from there to that Cornhill branch and were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Acle. W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 oler. It was a lovely branch that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 That was for his job again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, all the time, yes, 'cos he was on the railway all the time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh dear me. You could work - he was in his twenties. About twenty-eight I think. Well he was sixty-five when he died in - 1932. So work that back to 1890 when he married you see, I was born in '93. He was born, oh - he wa
s born in 1867. He was born 1867 so that - I was born '93. He was married the year before. Twenty-six he'd be - mother was older I that's was it, she's about twenty-eight I think. Twenty-eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 All Berwick born, they were Berwick, yes, all right the way through. All me ancestors are Berwick.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Your mother and your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, both yes. Called them - they were Millers, me mother, called them Miller. Go way back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What was your father's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 He was a - a delivery porter at the start.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 That was his first job was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes. And then finished up as a railway ticket collector at Central station {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Newcastle{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So he went from porter to ticket collector?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 To ticket collector at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Newcastle{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you know any jobs he had in between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
No. Just - Just on that - just that, yes, that's it. He did serve his time as a plumber, understand that, years before. For his health he - he - for his health he came off it and went on the railway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So he was an apprentice plumber?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 He had been - he'd served his time in Berwick and then he went on to the railway at Berwick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did he work as a plumber before he joined the railway, did he finish his apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Before - oh yes, he did - yes, for a bit but for his health he had to pack in. He just had gone to the railway just when I was born I think.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How many years do you think as he worked as a plumber?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well he must have - few years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Five or six after his apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Probably he - he would have you see if he'd served his time from fifteen. He must have been about ten years }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 plumbing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 . And then he - and then he - no, that's including his - that's right. Yes that's right, but - and then he started on the railway about 1892.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did he have any jobs after he became ticket collector or was this last job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 That was his only job, he went right the way through 'til he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you remember any casual jobs or part time jobs that he did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. No. Nothing, nothing, he hadn't any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you remember him ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
He wasn't. No, he was lucky. That's why they were on - that's why they wanted these jobs you see, after they were - things were that bad in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 building}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  trade. They just went on for security. He was all right on that, just on that one job all the - worked for the North Eastern Railway all the time. 'Til it was the L.N.E.R. at the finish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you remember when he changed his job from being a porter to being a ticket collector?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh that was 1914. Yes, when he came from .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 That's when he got that - promotion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, he got that promotion to Newcastle Central. And he was there 'til he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 She'd be two years older than me father so she must have been about twenty-eight I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 She came from Berwick on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Tweed{\*\xmlclose}. That's it, yes, well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did she have any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes, she was a - a dressmaker, served her time in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Berwick}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
. And - she wanted a - after she was out of her time she to Edinburgh and she was working in there when the Forth Bridge was opened, the railway bridge, 1890. She used to talk about that. It was a great even that, the railway brid
ge. She worked as a dressmaker, she's in charge - she was also in charge of some things that - I remember that the - Eynmouth it was the - the - big disaster with the fishermen and that. Tremendous - there was about a hundred fishermen all lost their live
s well they had the job to do all the - things for the widows and that you know. The widow's dresses and - had all them - them to make. It was a big event that. It was - that was in October, I forget what year it would be. Before she was married you know.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was that place called Eynmouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Eynmouth. Yes, over above - aye, in Berwickshire. A little fishing village. And all that were lost, it was a lovely morning and the ships all went out and - about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} it changed all of a sudden the whole lot we
re capsized and all that were lost. Aye, somewhere in the '90's. She used to talk about it, and then they got all the widows' things to make you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Dunlop\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , the people in Berwick that - they were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was she in charge of a shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 She was in char
ge of the - of the - in charge of the - doing the jobs you see, doing the dresses and that, in full charge of the - the stock. What you call a macklemaker in them times, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did she go back to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Edinburgh{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 That was in - no, she was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Edinburgh{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} after that, the disaster must have been before the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Forth{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Bridge{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 was opened. She was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Edinburgh{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} 1890. And then she got married in '92. At Berwick. Came back to Berwick again in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Dunlop\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  shop again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did she work after she was married then in that shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. She never worked again, no, when she was married she just settled down domestic work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did she have any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. She'd do a little bit - odd things you know now and then for herself but it - you couldn't say she took the trade up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you know what hours she worked as a dressmaker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
In those days. Oh they'd be long hours - there were - there was once like - I remember one Easter time, there were - in those days it was work you see, she used to work I shoul
d from half past eight in the morning 'til five. Weekends when there's anything - any event on, Easter time or something of that they - they worked right late, right on 'til {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midnight{\*\xmlclose}, to get jobs done, big orders and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 That was 1892 she finished?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye, that's right, 1892.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How many rooms were there in the house you lived in - which house were you in a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 This one. This last one, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you were a child I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh aye. Well I was four years at - was nearly four year at Tweedmouth and then four years at Newsholme.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Let's take Newsholme then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye, Newsholme was a little standard - the standard type railway house you know, was - three bedrooms }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 upstairs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , big living room }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 downstairs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
 and a big kitchen. Big pan
try and then everything was all - old fashioned, there was no water laid on or anything, in fact there was a railway engine tank at the end of the street, there was cottages, what they call railway cottages, and that was - you had to - to supply the water
 
for us. Used to bring - aye, take this - take the tank away and bring it full of fresh water. That got condemned that after when - that was later, we're back - I'm talking about - in the 90's then. We were there from about 1898 to 1902. And there was no g
as or anything, it was all paraffin oil. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did anybody else apart from your mother and father and you live in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, Just us -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, we hadn't then. Sometimes a relief fellow would be there, maybe a r
elief signalman or something. There was a lad I remember who came from Ferry Hill. He was a relief signalman and - I was only a kiddie that day - I used to think a lot of him. That was only - only time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your mother ever pay anybody to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. No, no. No, was nobody employed, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did she do her own washing or did she ever send it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, she done all - everything. Baking as well, done all bread like old fashioned it was. Every Friday. Monday was the washing day, 
then the washing and that. Aye, in fact it's funny, when I was a nipper about eighteen - I'd be eighteen months, it's one thing - everybody they have something to think back and I must have been only about eighteen months and that was in Tweedmouth. Now I
 
remember this, she had a big pan with a big handle and done the washing, just lifted it onto the fire. And I have recollections of that and I was in a cradle, I can just remember, in the wooden cradle in them days, aye. And then - and then the washing was
 done - that was only because you hadn't a set pot or anything at Tweedmouth, was only the one room downstairs and I think and a - a bedroom upstairs. At Tweedmouth, the railway houses were far better. There was more accommodation at Newsholme. And}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4850714  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 was better still where - we had trees in front of us and - you know, the hills at the back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You were only }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8590468\charrsid4850714 about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  three or four years old and you can remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I remember that one, oh aye, that was - that goes back to - first recollection of anything in - in life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your mother or your father mend or make clothes for you and themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh my father used to cobble the boots and that, cut me hair and that, oh yes, had to do that. Oh yes, she couldn't afford - afford barbers. Used to get the leather and cobble your boots, all that. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your father or mother make any clothes for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Well my mother made all mine. Made my suit 'til I was - left school. She made all me shirts, oh aye, been a macklemaker you know 'cos in them days that was her line. She done all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did they make their own clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 My mother made hers but my father had to get his tailor made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 He had them made for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 He generally did - well, in them days - both of them - well, he had t
o go to the tailor, there was very few - if you managed to - sometimes they were - you know in the shop - you get them to fit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What about shirts and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye. He would happen - mother made - she made them. She made all them, oh aye.
 Oh you had to in them days. Struggle. Well - the rent was only two and six and the wage was only sixteen bob a week. Now you think of that, on the top of sixteen pound now it's nothing. But - everything was cheap. Look what you could get for a penny. You
'd get a packet of fags for a penny. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Woodbines}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  they were.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You get nothing these days for a penny do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh no, the whole things different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your father help your mother with any jobs in the house like cleaning and cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes,
 I do - and washing - washing up and that and do a little bit of wall papering, anything, or bit painting. You had to do that yourself, your own decorating.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What about washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye, and he'd help a little bit, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, he didn't have - no, she done all that. Otherwise he'd get chased.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you were very small do you remember that your father got you ready in the mornings or}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8590468\charrsid4850714  undressed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  you at night or bathed you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, me mother did all that job. She done all that, aye, as far as I remember, aye yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your father ever read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Not much, it was more me mother. She was the one that was the reader. Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 aye}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes, 
sometimes - oh yes, we went to church. There was once I remember - the first - once we went to Carlisle, that's where I seen the first motor car, 1899. It was a three wheeler. It was at Carlisle station, I remember seeing the one - it was an old thing wit
h - it was 1899. Cars were hardly thought about then. That was just a trip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was he taking you out as he was working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, no, it was a holiday, went for the trip, for the day up from Newsholme, went- got the - the railway pass you see, I expect we
 could travel free them, from Newcastle to Carlisle. And back again. To Newsholme. We used to come in - used to come into Newcastle you know at the weekends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 With your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Father and mother. Three of us would come in. In fact I've got a photograph there with the - the group of us. Aye. Aye, it's there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your father ever look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh I wasn't - it wasn't necessary, she was always at home. Oh there's no going away - none - none of the ways of our wo
rking like what there is nowadays. None of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did she ever go into Newcastle for some shopping or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Blythe's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 . She used to go to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Blythe\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , from Newsholme, she used to go there, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 But you always used to go with her did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Sometimes, oh yes, many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I just wondered if your father looked after you when she was in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Blythe}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, he - he'd be on duty likely. In that time, and be back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have any particular jobs that you had to do at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Me? Well I didn't have all that much, I'd clean me own shoes and that. As a nipper like. Yes. Looked after yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 For example you didn't set the table or do the washing up on Sundays or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, no. No, she done all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you were a boy in Newsholme, did you have to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh I was generally in bed before eight o'clock every night. Oh yes. Never up later than nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your mother put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Generally. Oh yes, as far as I remember. Maybe I fell asleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have a bed to yourself and a bedroom to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, bedroom to myself. Three bedrooms }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 upstairs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  yes. Some had big families you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. Not in them days, there wasn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
There was no bath, we had to - one in front of the fire you know, you had the - the wrappings around you. Put the kettle on, get hot water and get a bath that way. Be nice and comfortable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have a special night for bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Just Saturdays generally. Saturday night generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have a special day when you used to change your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, I - you had the Sunday things, then you put the Sunday things way on the Sunday night and you put t
he other things on on the Monday again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were these clean things on Monday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, all the clean things once a week, oh yes. On a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where did you eat your meals, did you have a dining room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 It was all generally in the kitchen. Or t
he living room if necessary - if there was any company in the living but in the kitchen you could - had a table there and - side the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 But now and again you had a posh meal in the living room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Well in the - in the kitchen, there was a range you know and - and an oven and an open fire. Coaled up. Sometimes we made girdle scones and that with the flat girdle. Well it was - what they called Mother's Pride in them days, you see it on the vans no
w but it's only a name that, mother's pride, her bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What time of day did you have your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well it was early always. Seven o'clock, half past seven and that. Before you go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did the three of you sit down together?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Generally, oh yes, nearly always all meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you remember a typical breakfast, things you had to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh generally the bacon - bacon and - generally porridge for a start off. If I hadn't have porridge at - last thing at night when 
you got the milk fresh from the farm. But that was at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4850714  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
that where we lived like that, you know, go to school then from - I was - I was nine when we shifted there, to , and then I had three mile to walk to school. That was different altogether. The same acco
mmodation you know. But everything was - done at home, all the - everything was cooked and meals and everything. And I had to carry - sandwich and that to school. There wasn't any - like what they've got nowadays. We had to carry - cocoa for your - you kn
o
w, in a bottle, an enamel bottle, used to get that warmed at the fire. The school had just two fires, one to corner - each corner at the fire - one big room. It's a new school and all. But - you had to carry everything. As well as lessons. What lessons th
ere was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So for breakfast you'd normally have porridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Porridge}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  and - bacon and eggs, aye. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What did you drink with your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh just tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you remember what your normal lunch was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well I had sandwiches, when you used to come back you'd get a - a dinner you know, be potatoes and meat and - and beef and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So weekdays you had sandwiches at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I carried the - but I got me dinner really when I came back, you see. I land back home about five, I'd 
leave school about four. Had to walk the three miles back. And then you - the dinner was ready cooked for us. Father and mother had their dinner at dinnertime and then I get mine at the time when I came in. Potatoes and cabbage and meat, you know, everyth
i
ng - greens and everything. Well you're living in the country, we had our own garden with all produce you see. All - all potatoes and all that. All good stuff. The flour was good as well them days. You didn't take half as much - take a loaf of bread, you 
nearly have to eat two now before you feel full, with a couple of slices of homemade bread and you were satisfied, was that good. Such a difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have anything different on certain days, for example on Sundays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Sundays, oh aye, we had
 - kit was a real happy dinner on a Sunday, they'd always roast beef on a Sunday. As far as you could get it. Yes, I - it was cheaper in them days, it - for all we had a small wage and that we seemed to live all - all right as far as food was concerned, i
t was - good. Aye, you had less but what you had was - was good, you seemed to be more satisfied, there wasn't so much - well there was a lot - the shops hadn't sweets or anything like that. Oh no, you seemed to be - well I've never really had a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 doctor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , me.
 Been lucky in that way, I - it's open air, to the working man and - the trade as well, keeps you fit. Being in the open all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Your mother made her won bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did she make any jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes. Many a time, oh aye. You'll not kno
w what Scottie apples are do you? They're the wild - wild ones, you know, they see them on the roadside somewhere around there, small ones and they're hard. Used to make them - or crabapples - we called them scrummies up there. Crabapples, the small ones,
 we made that crabapple jelly and others you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Bramble}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
 jelly and that, used to go and get the brambles and they make it. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your mother do any bottling of fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Preserve them? No. We didn't, no, we didn't preserve them any no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Pickles, sometimes they'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 pickle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  some onions, not very often though. Pickled onions. You grow onions and pickle them, oh yes. Sometimes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did they make any wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, sometimes ginger wine. Sometimes made
 that at - Christmastime. But those others, they had their own hens and - platelayers - and two platelayers they had a pig each. Used to feed the pig up and then they used to kill it and - and get the bacon of it, that's - right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you lived near Wooler, were you in railway cottages then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How many railway workers were there altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There, there was four railway cottages there. We had fourteen cottages at Newsholme, but there was only four railway cottages in that 
- there was the station house. It's still there. And there's the railway cottage, but all the others gone, the whole station's gone and everything. And - it was the same, three rooms }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 upstairs}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  and two down. All stone built, a lovely stone built job. Real country built, well built. And - water supply was a pump around at the back. And it used to freeze up in the winter.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you keep any animals at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Just a cat. Same as I had rabbits - just for pets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Not for eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. No, we didn't bother anything. They did with the - and up at the farm there they had cows and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you remember how many times a week you had meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Practically every day we had - some - something like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Usually beef or did you have all different sorts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 It was beef generally. Sometimes mutton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Very little. When I was a child, no, very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever do any poaching for rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I did once, it was for salmon, went out for salmon.
 But I had no right to go out, it was right way up - College Water. Near Cheviot. And - I just had been a year at the trade and I were apprentice and we had to do some jobs at two farms. One night that - some fellows asked if I would go out with them. And
 
- it was to do - we didn't know what it was for and it was big - these big hill, shepherds came down, it's about ten of them all together and we went down this College Water. Well - we had a gaff on each end with three points, you see, you had a gaff and 
y
ou could stab a salmon with it. And we had couple of flayers as well. And - one fellow was gassed, he's well canned up. And it - it was a frosty night and the moon was up and there was a plank across the - he thought he'd go to the other side of the river
 and he gets onto this plank and he slips off in the middle and he slips into the river, well that - that sobered him up. But well, right the way down to Heathborough we only got three, there'd been another lot there before us. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 They came up from a place called Durrow near - up Killom way and they had cleared them all before this and - it's all illegal you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
And I always remember that as a kid.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 But you didn't do that regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. Never went with them any more. We had salmon - when I was there 
we had salmon for breakfast, salmon for dinner and salmon for tea. Every year there was salmon - there's plenty of it you see and cost them nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you remember your mother having less food than you and your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 We had at Newsholme but 
it was struggle sometimes. Aye. She used to be - make - make ends meet. Oh aye, sometimes. Never - we were real - never really hard up, we were never unemployed or anything, there was others that - very hard up when they got unemployment, nothing coming i
n at all. In the building trade then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your father usually have more to eat than you two at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh no, just the same. All the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes, we were free and easy. Yes, no - there's no hard }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 regulations}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 . No rules.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Could you choose what you wanted to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes. If you could get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 They didn't say you'd got to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There were times were but - there wasn't much of everything but what there was it was good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Suppose there's carrots you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye, yes, oh yes, I could eat anything, leave or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Could you say to your mother, I don't want any carrots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh I didn't - I - I canna remember ever complaining - it was always good - it were all -
 there was never any trouble with eating. If it was peas it was peas, it was carrots it was carrots, only eat about - it all - all went down. There was never anything left, there was never any complaints.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 If you wanted something like the salt did you just reach and get it or did you say, will you please pass the salt?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh you just got it - just the same as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Could you ask for second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I canna remember but - I expect - I can't remember asking. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have to hold your knife and fork in a special way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh aye, taught 'em to - oh yes, you had to be - careful how you handle these.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 And sitting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes. Sit erect if you can. Be a good boy, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Could you bring toys or a book to the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. No, no. Oh no, didn't have any toys or anything like that, no. Nothing at the table, there was nothing put on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Just when we'd all finished. Aye. Except if there was company in, well - you know, you'
d ask to leave the table. No, other times didn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Usually you all sat down together at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes. All the three of us, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you always have the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes. Generally. Oh yes. Each have their own position.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your mother always serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes. Always. Made it and served it and everything, washed 'em up as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Who did she serve first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Father I think and then - generally. I'd be last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was your mother an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8590468\charrsid4850714 easy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes, good company. Oh yes. Well read - a good reader she was. You know, what there was in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 affectionate?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 If you were worried about anything could you talk to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye. Oh yes, you could explain everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 He was all right. Easy going - took - took things easy. Nothing worried him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Could you tell him about things that worried you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes, you could tell either of them, both - mum was the best naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh well - you had to show all affection. Oh yes, all right, you just all liked each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No special things that they insisted on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, there wasn't anything - no. I might
 have been get - well with being an only one probably inclined to be spoiled I think. Aye. Only one generally is aren't they. Aren't they, so they say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your parents say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, I - I never - 
no, that was - I think that was a fault that, I hadn't to - no, never encouraged you getting into - any trouble any way. Never encouraged - fighting or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What if another child hit you, did they expect you to go away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well they'
d - but they never encouraged it. No, no, never encouraged me that way. Couldn't see any point in hurting anybody. But that - that was put in - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What kind of person do you think your parents wanted you to grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well, just - ordinary. Play the game. Upright and straight and - be honest and tell the truth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Did they make you think that some things in life are very, very important?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There was - oh there was lots of things. Not go - not to go stealing or anything like that,
 the thing that others would. Things - not to take anything that wasn't yours. Be honest and be straight. Tell the truth.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What did they think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh they detested it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 
My mother was inclined to be - you know - she - she did go to church at Wooler and that, all of us there, she's inclined to be that way. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Good living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you had company, if grown ups were talking, could you just join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh sometimes, yes, oh yes, oh - it all depends. Not - you know, not - you know, you hadn't to talk - out of place. That would be rude.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 If you did something that your parents didn't like what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I'd get a hiding, I'd gat a swipe off of the old chap with - a clout. Done anything -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 In your - in your bottom. Send you flying in a minute. You know, if you got a little bit - inclined to be unruly like all kids at times.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 That was your dad did that was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 He would, aye, but not very often. I used to dodge him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your mother ever do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh aye, I've seen her sometimes, done something that I shouldn't have done. Get a smack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did they ever use a stick or a strap or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, no, none of that. Oh no, no. Got that at school. Beaten with a belt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were you hit very often by your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 No, very, very seldom. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There was no call for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you remember any particular occasion when you were hit by your dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. There was nothing, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you remember how you felt when they hit you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well I remember onc
e, it was going to school and I got up late. Must have been late and I was just taking me time, me mother gave me a swipe and - I knew I was going to be late for school as it was and - well I done that, I always remember that and - think they - they took 
i
t out of her as well because - whether it happened I just was taking me time and - instead of - didn't see the point in hurrying and yet I landed at school late and then I got a - got a whacking when I got to school for landing in late. Got the double dos
e.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Would you say that you got your ideas about how to behave more from your mother or mote from hour father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye, yes, from me father - more from me mother, oh aye. Generally you find that don't you. Mother plays a big part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you had a birthday was it different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well - no, very - wasn't much - different. I was living in the country, there wasn't much - didn't make any special do of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you get any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Sometimes - oh the presents sent and that, through the post and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Might - might make a cake sometimes. Mother would make a cake - you know, birthday cake. That'd be all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever have any guests for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, very seldom. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you remember anything that you did with your mother and father on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Always in - just all together. Probably have some company up from - some of the relations would be up from Berwick. Used to be up somewhere at Christmas time staying with us, unc
les and aunts, used to come, different ones on both sides you see. Both mother's side and me father's side and used to have - both at Newsholme and - there - Wooler way, up here as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 That piano. That one. 1911. That's a Victorian one that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was it bought in 1911?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
It wasn't new, that was second hand then. Made in Edinburgh. However is - must be over a hundred years old that. I got it in 1911, I can play by ear a bit and that was the only music we had in our house. Aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Could your mother or father play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. No, just I could - rattle on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 piano}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  - made a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did anybody sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Me mother was always singing. Oh aye, she - sing anytime but not - but you know, g
o round the house singing, she was always singing. There's the things I used to catch what she used to sing. Remember them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever play the piano for her to sing to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, I - no, she never - I would hear her humming away maybe while I'd be 
- sometimes she'd be humming away to - but I'd only be playing this. Anyway any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your parents play any games with you, either in the house or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 outside}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Sometimes. Mother was good - cards and that, she used to tell fortunes for a bit of f
un. Aye. It's - girls in and tell 'em when they're going to get married and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, oh we had books, yes. Mother had some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Lots of books or what kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well there's - different novels. By George Elliot and them. Aye. I forget now, there were a lot -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There were your mother's books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 She - my mother - she was a great reader. Oh aye. Florence Nightingale, I've got them in there, Life of Florence Nightingale and all that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What about newspapers, did you get any newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
We used to get the - I think there's the North Mail used to come. Used to get the North Mail, we couldn't get the Chronicle up there. Used to get the Chronicle in Newcastle.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What about weekly papers or Sunday papers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
We didn't have any Sunday papers up there, there was no trains or anything on a Sunday. There was no trains on a Sunday at Newsholme, never was in that line time. There was not any trains on that line you know. You can tell they closed down i
t had gone a hundred and forty years. There's a lot doesn't go that far, the buses and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Never any trains?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There was no passenger trains from Mars to Blyth or Ashington on a Sunday. There wasn't anything in Cornhill where we were in - near Woole
r. Just six trains - six trains a day there, six day a week. Now they've got buses and - every day of the week. And they're maybe - off the road now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you get any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 magazines}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There was one - didn't get 'em, used to see one. What did they call 
it again. It went to - he went down on the Titanic. Oh dear me - Review - Review of - Reviews, I think that was the title of it. Great magazine. What did they call him, was it - well he went down with it - oh dear, I've forgotten his name, he went down in
 
the Titanic in 1912. I remember seeing that. I'll tell you how I seen it, it used to come to - and we used to get a glance at it, and it was a schoolmasters book, the only magazine that used to come, it was very good. In them days, you know, magazines wer
e
 hard to get. She used to get - we went - used to go for Maple Darrit to do the - you know, the shopping, on a Saturday and go to W.H. Smith's and get the People's Friend. I used to get a comic, Jack Sam and Pete. In them days, aye. W.D. Stead was the - t
h
e chap, aye, and he went down in the Titanic. - W.D. Stead, aye. Oh they used to get a weekly - we used to get a weekly paper, the Berwick Advertiser, that used to come regular. Give you all the local news, then there was our Guardian. Used to see that an
d just had it back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were you nearer to Annett then you were to Wooler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Just half and half. Oh Wooler, oh yes. Wooler was nearly three mile away. But it was half way between Berwick and Annett. You see, Wooler is half way between Berwick and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Annett}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
. It's fifteen each way. Annett's thirty from Berwick. And we could go to Annett or go to Berwick. Sometimes we went to Berwick for the shopping. Sometimes to Annett. The local town's three miles away, aye, we must - there was no shops to speak of w
here we were, it was just the big farm and the hills at the back. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Acle hill's just up above nearly two miles away, up - up here.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You said your mother did a lot of reading?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 And she read to you as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes, oh aye, when I was a kiddie, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you remember any funerals in the family when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh yes, we had one at Acle. An uncle of mine - me mother's youngest brother, he was in the Yorkshire Post, he was a printer - his brother was the head overseer his eldest brother. And he took very ill, at Leeds and he - he landed, he came back. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Came}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
 back by train, how he got - me mother went and met him on the train changed at Allenmouth to get our train at Allencain and up to the Cornhill branch and he - he was only 
with us a fortnight, 1910, August he came and he died on August Bank Holiday I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you remember who went to the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye, we did - me father and - we took it through - he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 buried}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  in Berwick, we took it by coach - by the road to 
- my boss at that same time he done the funeral job you see. And we went to Tweedmouth and met the - others at Tweedmouth and then walked right up to Berwick }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 cemetery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  where he was buried, and although there's - the - the family joined in there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How many people were at the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh twenty or thirty there. They were relatives. Both sides.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What kind of clothes did they wear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 All black. And the horses were all in black for the hearse and that. And then they - the Town Hall - th
e - the bell used to ring, like a curfew used to ring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you wear black for a while afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You wore - generally wore for another six months, wore black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Black everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye, black tie and black - everything all in black - clo
thes. Deep mourning they were - everybody went into deep mourning then. Prior to 1914. Oh its different altogether now, it's all cars and all light things different. Oh '14 was changed everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you were a child can you remember going out visiting neighbours or friends or relatives?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh yes, used to go to neighbours and that. Used to join in - play with them and that. There was bigger families. There was one family of five I used to play with and used to go to school with and all that. Next one was only one there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was that a railway family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 They were all railway people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you go shopping with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye, I went - we went to Wooler but generally like on a Saturday - or Berwick on a Saturday, whichever - if there
 was any shopping went. We could go to Mollett, you know had a market pass you see to travel - do the shopping in Shirley Market pass by there, and owing to one of the family I used to get free as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was it always your mother who did the shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 She done the all the shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You told me that you went out with your father to Carlisle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 To Carlisle once and it was from Newsholme, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever go anywhere on Bank Holidays or any other holidays, on outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh not - we
ll - where - we used to go on our holidays used to go away - remember going to - 1904 going to - Scarborough, that was before - you know Scarborough, well I remember when it was built. 1904. Like Scarborough, used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  there to Mrs Thornton's. George's pe
oples place you know. His father and I were great pals, he died five years ago. And - oh it was - I remember it, that morning drive, wonderful that you know. 1905 when it was opened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have holidays every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, we had a week's holiday. Used to go to odd people, they had - we paid for it you see }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
 that made a difference. Then we had free passes. That's how we travelled in them days, you couldn't - we never seen any - Blackpool and - Llandudno and all over the place. I was lucky. I was lucky as a kid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your mother and your father always go with you on your holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, always. Right up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 And you went all over everywhere?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where we went - where we went for a holiday - yes. Scarborough, Bridlington, Blackpool, Southport, Llandudno. Several times at }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Scarborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , several times at Blackpool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What kind of things did you do when you were holidaying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh just went to - we had entertainment and that and - had a bit paddle in the water and - used to go - have en
tertainment then like anybody, you know, just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you tell me something about how you spent your Saturdays when you lived in Wooler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh I used to on me bike, another chap, the station master's son and I we used to cycle a lot around that way. Oh used to go to - different }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 places}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 . Climbing hills and that, climbing up }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Acle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , Yevering Bell and all that, it was all interesting you know. There's plenty of walks and walking we were always on the move, I was - away hunting for things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Sundays was quiet. Used to get on the bike as well on Sundays. Go away cycling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How old were you when you started cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Fifteen. Aye. Fourteen to fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Before you started going out cycling how did you spend Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh just playing about - playing about there. Going up in the hills and that and - up the river and that. It was all, you know, real country like all the time, you just made the most of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You said you had different clothes on on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you were playing around you had to get changed again did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh well, there wasn't much on - if I was riding the cycle - we was cycling see I was bit - I was fifteen, well you just had other things on, you didn't put your best things on yo
u just changed for to go - on the cycle road somewhere. I remember once we cycle to Ingram where the - the allies were stationed once, that was going through Wooler way, you know just, here - south this way. The troops - Ingram. Aye. You see it up the Woo
ler Road, you turn - you turn left as you're going north. Went up this and - it was just to see the camp there and the allies were there. Remember one fellow - one of the times he says - dearly beloved brethren we are }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8590468\charrsid4850714 here}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  today and gone tomorrow. One of the troops. We were only young you know, it was enough to make you join up with all these attractions and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your parents think it was wrong if you did any work on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Generally oh I didn't - objected to it but that generally graduall
y broke down. That way - 1914-18 did very little of that - everything was very quiet on a Sunday. And never done anything on a Sunday. Not even - not even gardening in them days. Prior to 1914. After the '14 war everything seemed to change. Different, bro
ke everything down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your parents think it wrong for you to play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
They did, they thought it was wrong, oh yes, even cycling was bad enough but we - we were off, we're away. They didn't like the idea, no. Not if they saw you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did they both go to church on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
No, very seldom. Where we were - they used to when they were young, they'd all have their - their own pews and that at Berwick you know when they were young they were brought up very - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 rigid}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  to what -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were they Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Presbyterian. Both families and - but to different churches. The - father's people they went one - Wallace Green at Berwick and me mother's went another chapel in - Chapel Street they called it, they - they had their own pew for 
the families. Aye, they were very strict. They were. As far as I was concerned I never was been as a kiddie, I made trouble at - I'd been taken to Wallis Green church and - I couldn't stand all the noise, you know, the singing and all that and all - and I
 started to yelling out and I got - got chased out, I got a right thumping when I got outside but - I upset the apple cart. I always remember that, I couldn't stand the noise. No. Seemed unnatural.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I did - a little bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
I did I had to go to Wooler. Then we had a trip once with the Sunday school trip to Arnmouth. It was by train. And - I got on the train I remember looking out the train about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3627753\charrsid4850714 Withenshaw}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , I got a hot cinder in me eye, that was the 
end of that like. So I remember we got to Arnmouth it was teaming of rain. It was a right days outing that, what with the - the cinder in me eye from the engine and the - and the wet day, I was - I never liked Arnmouth some more after that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you go on many of these Sunday school trips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh just - that's about the only one I remember. Was too - you had to walk you know to the Sunday school and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you take part in any other things organized by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. No. I never was at
tached to the church, my mother used to go to the - Kirk Newton, that was a parish church, there was a big wedding there once. One from Fort Castle. I remember that, that was a big do that. I remember - hymn that was sung for the lady - Lady - it was}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8590468\charrsid4850714  Lady Joyce, she was one of the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
 Joyces getting married and she had 'O Jesu I have promised'. That was the - what she - the music that she fancied for her wedding piece. It seemed funny. That was at - that was at Kirk Newton - parish church. We went - that was ou
r near parish church you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So you didn't belong to anything connected with the church at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you say grace at mealtimes at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were you taught to say your prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I was but it faded away. Oh yes, as a youngster. It just faded away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your father take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 He didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Tory. For a long time, then he was Labour at the finish when he came up here. I made him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Why do you think he was Tory at first -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Well his father had been a Tory before him, me mother, they were Liberals. And they were Tories and - and that was - Berwick was a real - Liberal stronghold really. Annett was Tory you know. Annet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 t.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4850714  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Duke of Northumberland. Aye, they were Tory. He was a Tory at first.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
She was Liberal. In her views. A great Sir Edward Greer supporter. A great Sir Edward Greer supporter. In them days he was he fellow up - up - north, he was well liked.
 He was foreign secretary when the fourteen war broke. He went blind after, he was fine fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 With your mother was it a matter of family tradition, they were always Liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 More or less, yes, right through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you remember either of them voting in a general election before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh no, 1919 when the women got it, that's right, they hadn't it - I remember all about the suffragettes, was a joke. We had been to Blackpool and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 came}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  back, what would be 1912. Well you had to leave your handbags and everything outside - you know the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 York Minster}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  - and suffragettes were, you know, playing havoc then, trying to get in. Aye. Remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you - remember your mother or your father voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 These times - they just had - they had to go to Kirk Newton to vote you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you know which parties they voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
That's where - well that would be the one would vote Tory I should think and the other one vote Labour - Liberal. I think - I'm not sure whether they both voted for
 Sir Edward Greer, I think they would. That was the first time I heard Sir Edward Greer, 1906, he was speaking in Millfield School there, I always remember that and then - then I took an interest in politics. And me old boss, he was a great Liberal. And h
e used to get arguing - arguing with the others from Branston, they were stonemasons and they were strong Tories and - sparks used to fly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where was this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Millfield. Mill - Millfield, yes, that's not far from the Battle of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Flodden}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 . You know - you've heard tell of the Battle of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Flodden}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
? 9th of September, 1513. They put the stone up, headstone up for it - four hundred years after, 1913. I remember that, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where were you living when you went to this school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Living at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4850714  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 when I went
 to that school. I started at Newsholme then I was only a year and then we shifted up to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4850714  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
and then I finished - I went to school at Millfield form 1902. And - finished like at fifteen, then I started serving me time. That's in Gelngill}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 (?)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Not in Wooler - it's away from Wooler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 It's all away from - it all the way on. See, Millfield's opposite Wooler, towards Fall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How far away is that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 It's three mile again. You see, you got Wooler here and you've got}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4850714  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 there, Millfield's across here and you go across the Ford and then you - there's the Tweed and Berwick away across that way. You've got the hills all round here. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Kirk}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  Newton's away that way again you see, along the hills, but Wooler here and then here's - there was - all the different hills 
here up in Hedgup and Even Hill and - and Yevering Bell, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8590468\charrsid4850714 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
ig one. George has been up, he knows them well. Then like there's a little glen. Called Glen Deer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you know if your father ever felt and kind of pressure from his employers to vote for one party rather than another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh no, there was none of that in the railway now. Might have been if he'd been where he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 before}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 . Working for private firm, see, different. Oh there was none of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did he ever belong to any political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 He didn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did he ever help any political party at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, not - he never took any action - never active - any active part - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 She didn't take any active part but she - she - you know, she used to follow anything up, what was happening. Read up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was she always a keen Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 She was a keen Liberal, oh yes, she wasn't a Tory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When your parents weren't working how did they spend their time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh reading and that. Generally reading. Just sitting and reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your mother have any interests outside the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, there wasn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So she never went out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, didna - not - just - it was all open country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well he finished at half past eight, he's on from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 half}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  past six in the morning, finish at half past eight at night. Long days, aye, sixteen bob a week. Them were the days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did he always stay at home in the evening after he'd finished work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
He did, aye. Oh yes, never went far. That's right, just he had a talk - he have a crack with somebody outside, some of the - you know, the neighbours maybe before he went to bed - in the summer. In the wintertime it was different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did he ever go to a club or a pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. Sometimes go to Wooler maybe for a glass. Yes, it's only place that was nearest pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did he go very regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. Very seldom. Once or twice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your mother ever go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, not - not to drinking, she was teetotal, she was dead against it, she's a Good Templar. She's strong against drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your father take any part in sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, there wasn't any - no. There wasn't anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you remember him ever going to races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did he ever bet?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
She didn't follow - he never bet, no, dead against it. Oh they were both dead against anything like that, gambling or anything or betting or anything. Dead against it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did they belong to any clubs such as a sick club or a funeral club or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There wasn't them days, no. They - there was - no, there wasn't any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Any savings club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh there was just ordinary - insurance fellows that came round you know, it's only - you can call that a club. A
ye. Just insured and - aye, there was them things, aye. But - well I paid - a penny or a - penny a - a week it used to be. And we get eighteen quid, it 'll take nearly a hundred and eighteen to bury us now, in this day. It's terrible. I knew one - one par
ty - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 wife's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
 - me first wife's father, when he died he was ninety two, he was a Sunderland chap, he died in Heaton. He died at ninety-two, he had paid - what - about what - they'd paid thirteen pound in - no, no, I've got the wrong one. I paid twenty-sev
en pound in and only drew thirteen over his years you see and that's what - he only got thirteen - and that - it was fixed at thirteen and - that - Royal London I think it was insurance company. But - we see - that's the way they tell you. You could have 
- dropped dead the next week and you'd have still got the - the full thirteen pound. But you paid twenty-six shilling and got a - like over his years. Aye, insurance companies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Who did you play with when you went out as a child to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh the - 
the stationmaster's son and I we were - great pals. And other - the other lads and the other neighbours' boys we went to school with. We just played at anything, cricket or anything, well we - you know, like all lads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were they all railway people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 All railway people, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where did you play, in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Just - no, just in the fields outside, 'cos it's all fields where we were. No town at all, it's all just - you know. Sometimes played with other lads up at the farm. The big - there 
was a big farm there, Charters was the farmer - he was a wealthy farmer. He'd a big farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Not that far, there wasn't any dirt to dirty you. It was all clean there. The air was clean and everything 
else was clean. All - in the fields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 But if you got all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 muddied }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Sometimes you did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you get into trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, we never got into - much trouble there. Not like the town lads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Could you play with anybody you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes, we all did. As long as you got on all right with them. It's up to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So there was nobody that your parents tried to stop you from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, no, there was no objections. No restrictions. Everybody was go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 o}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 d pals. We all knew each
 other in the country you know, knew each other for miles. Right away, even other villages you all knew who - what was happening, who was who. That was the beauty. Didn't even in one street you don't know each other in the city but in the country you know
 each other right away beyond other villages. Different altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you belong to any youth clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I didn't, no. I didn't. I never joined in. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 
Our village had a Boys' Brigade but I never joined it.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was that not a club you were in when you went cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh just went with friends, just cycling away, exploring, went to Kelso or somewhere where we went on the - you know - onto the - across to - to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Keele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  and that. Or Doddington way or anywhere, just round about - in them days it was all r
ight. There was nothing on the road. The roads were bad like, it smashed several springs easy, there were pot holes. Then the dust used to fly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 But it was quieter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh it was all quiet and nice. Now it's noisy, the aircraft - you can't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 
believe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  it
's the same district when the air - aircraft - it echoes you know. Yes. Oh it was all peace itself. Especially if you got up the hills, climbed up, way up, you could see for miles. You could see the sea in the distance, fifteen miles away. From the top of
 hills and that. You know. Up several times. Used to be - you had to watch for adders - in among the grass, you had to be careful and you - but I was - I was never - touched with any. I was fortunate to be all right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have any hobbies when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I can't say I'd hobbies at school. I did get on with photography after - as a hobby, about 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 But not when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Not when at school, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Ah - oh yes, we had a cat and
 then we used have - had a rabbit as well for a bit. Until I - I didn't - forgetting to feed the thing and that's the way - it was the end of the rabbit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you collect anything ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. No, no, I never - no, I didn't take any interest that wa
y, not - not - I did - I did - eggs, oh yes, we used to - I had a - I had a lot of different eggs used to get you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Birds\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  eggs. Oh aye, had a - had a - a case of them. I had quite a lot. And the stationmaster's son and I, we used to go - and got a lot
 of - tom tit and titmice and - starlings and the whole lot. Blackheaded seagulls and the lot. Aye, they were good. But we - we - you get them along by the wayside you know. Swallows. We used to have a swallow used to come at the end of the house, we'd ho
n
eysuckle up and in the - used to come there every summer, this swallow. And the swallow's nest was up in the corner there. And the honeysuckle hanging down there. It's nice - nice when you opened the window and - and the garden used to be wallflowers and 
that and you'd get the - you know, the - scent coming off the flowers and that, off the wallflowers and that. Sweet peas and that and the honeysuckle used to be nice in the summer. Different to the smell of - diesel fumes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh we had a garden, my mother used to look after the flowers and that and we had the other garden along the railway side, we planted potatoes generally at Easter time you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I have done a bit, of that - planted leeks and car
rots and all that - turnips and that. Although there's plenty turnips in the fields, used to be good. Used to throw them off the carts as they go, bang on the door, now they charge }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 
eighteenpence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  for - for a turnip. Eeh it's all money isn't it. Feed the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 fish with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  the - feed the sheep with them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You said you went fishing, did you go often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh no, that time - fishing that was more or an accident than anything else as went with these fellows. Right up College Water, George knows that part, College Water you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 But it was only now and again was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh it was only - only - where we done repairs and - that's - that particular night was in the December 1909.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 But did you go fishing other than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I never bothered, there's others
 did. Some went fishing. I once went out with some - with some fishers, I remember - that came up from Newcastle and - they asked me to go with them. I had to get permission and - in our glen get permission from Copeland Castle, that's how these - I went 
with them. Another time I went baiting. You know, with a - a - that wasn't much of a game either. I only went the once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You went cycling a lot didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye. - Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever go walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I done a lot of walking. More walking than anything. It was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 walking}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 . Oh aye. They've forgot how to walk nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I mean walking for pleasure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Yes. Just for pleasure, that's right, oh it was grand to go up the hills there. You were always walking somewhere. There seemed - every time you 
went out there was always something to - something happening wasn't there. See you're among nature, there's life, life in the very hedgerows. Just see weasels and all sorts of things. Wasps. And - there was - used to - if you smashed a wasp}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8590468\charrsid4850714 \rquote s nest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  up you had it. You upset the lot of them. It's daft to do that. Done t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8590468\charrsid4850714 hat just to go to - you know go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  to school and - get the lot around you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I didn't, no, there was no sports up there, just - me own sport you know as ki
ds and that, there was nothing - too far - there was - Newcastle United used to be playing and that but it was too far away.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Not there, we used to come to Newcastle. Come by train to a pantomime. Oh yes. Remembe
r - oh yes. Concerts and that. If there was anything on at Wooler you'd go in. There was no pictures or anything then. Sometimes I - if there's anything on in Wooler you'd go in to see it. But Newcastle was the - main attraction, once or twice a year for 
seeing the pantomimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When was the first time you went to the cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh up here in Newcastle. When }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Charlie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  Chaplin started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 About 19 - 1914, 1915. The war was on then. Charlie Chaplin was coming }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 into}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  the - first films I saw was here. When we - we moved to Newcastle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you get any pocket money when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
No. Not a penny. I was just telling the wife that the other day. I never expected any. It was no good, money was no good. I remember once when I
 was a kiddie at - Berwick, at me grandma's. There was an elderly lady there from Aberdeen, a canny old body, and she gave me a penny and I flung it on the floor. And I got a right hiding for that. I didn't want a penny. It was - it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 independent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  - the kids, they'll do anything for money now. There was no shops you see, you didn't want it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did anybody outside the home help your mother to look after the house or family, relations or friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, that wasn't necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Suppose your mother was ill or had to stay in bed how did you manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Well we just managed - we were fortunate enough to be all right. Until we got to Newcastle when she did take ill. That was a stroke. That was the finish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. They were all in Berwick. Both sides. All in Berwick. We just lived - that's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your parents have any particular friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were there one or two people who often used to call and see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh just the neighbours - round - there's some at the farm, we knew - you know, just ordinary neighbours. See them and they used to come down and see us. Have a crack with them every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You used to see them every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes. Just a little few - you know what it's like in the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your father have any special friends that you mother wasn't so friendly with for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh there wasn't anything like that, no, just - Just ordinary neighbourly people. And you went into their house and they came into ours.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever invite them into the house and give them something to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh sometimes. Oh they'd have a cup of tea and that at times. Different - just the neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How about coming in for a meal like dinner or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh no, it was - no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Any particular days when you might invite them in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well you'd have - we'd have people coming up with an excursion trip from Berwick or somewhere, you get - you
 get the likes of that you know in the country. They used to come. Some of them stay for a day or two. But that was all relations you see, me father's brothers or me mother's - side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did the people who lived nearby call in casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 These were j
ust the neighbours and that. Casually, that's right. Sometimes call - you know, come and have a cup of tea and - people - just around about. That's the one thing about the country, you all know each other, know each other practically for miles away. Next 
village. If you - just come and just drop in, have a bit of crack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What did your parents used to do for amusement in the days before radio, television and cinema?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh played cards and - you'd just sort of a sing-song among yourselves. Just made t
he most of it. There was nothing else, you hadn't - you had to make your own entertainment. That's how the piano came in. Aye. That piano only cost a pound. I suppose them - in them days, aye. I don't know what it cost to build it, I don't know, but we go
t it for a pound. That was 1911.- It's still there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Lots of people divide society into different groups.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Different social classes, did you think of some people belonging to one class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes, definitely. I was 
right in among them. Aye, Fort Castle, the one up there. Oh aye, they were different. Well they were different class altogether. The Joyce's took it over from the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Waterford's}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 . Lady Waterford and Fort Castle, that was her done all the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 oil paintings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
 in the school, Biblical }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 oil paintings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
, you've heard tell of it, in Fort - - in the Forge school. There's another new school built since then. Well they were another class altogether, even the big farmers, where Mr Charters was a farmer, at , well he used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8590468\charrsid4850714 take}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
 students round with him. Naturally he was away above - our side. There was two distinct - lots of people. You were really among the working class here they were - what you might call the elite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So there were just these two groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Two groups, a
lways were right in the country. Yes. I remember the Lanes of Eaton Manor, they had - the footmen and - you know, and - and the groom. And the hat and the cockade, well they had the white bands round their hats and the cockade up on the side of them, that
 
was in time of the horses. They were definitely - away from us. The Grays of Milford Hill are the same as - same family as Sir Edward Gray, of Falloden. The same Grays. Oh yes. They were at Milford Hill. He had a big staff of about fourteen or fifteen. I 
worked in that place when I served me time. Many time - sent up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Which class did you say you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well we belonged to the working class wouldn't we. The others, you can call them the - the feudal lords if you like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What kind of people, apart from the railway people, belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well the farm people - the - the farm - the big farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did they belong to the same class as you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes, well we were - we were all classed the same. All - use
d to join in with each other if there was any little bits of - does on, we all joined in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So belonging to the same class as you you've got the railway people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye, and the family, all the - all the same like us but - we might have been a little 
bit - a little bit above those being on the railway because the railways were looked as something in those days, they were means of getting you somewhere and getting away. You really look - it was well looked up to and the people on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort different from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, no, I was not - nothing - never anything like that. No, just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What about these feudal lords?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well you didn't - I - that was - I had no room for them really. They were a little bit away and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were you ever told to touch your cap or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 That's what I - yes, asked to do it and I wouldn't. I didn't - personally I thought I was just as good as anybody, whether they were in our 
class or not and I - I got into trouble for it because I wouldn't salute them and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Who were you asked to salute?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You had to. Oh there was - one - Swann they called him. The one at - near York Manor, you're supposed to salute him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Who told you to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
My - me boss, he said - I said, why should I? I said, I don't salute you so why should I salute him? I said, you're as much importance to me as his. That was the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 foreman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  - that was the joiner in the - in the country where I served me time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was your boss annoyed about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well he - he said it would be better - might help like to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 fetch}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  his trade, that was the only thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was there anybody that you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 They were. You always sir - yo
u sirred them. The Grays of Milford, that's who you sirred. If you met them you said - you had to say sir. You were expected to say sir.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 If you met who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Any of these peoples, I was talking about the Grays of Milford Hill. That class of people all the time. Ordinary people you didn't need to.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did anyone show particular respect to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh no, there was none of that with us. Oh no. We didn't expect it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Who were the most important people in this area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well the farmer a
t the - our village was the main - Mr Charters. He was the - most important, you know, all - the - all them big farmers all round, each one was - just as important as the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you meet these people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes, used to - meet them. Well I used to get on the - I was on the farms doing jobs for them. Doing repairs and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Why would you say these people were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well it's - it's - it's the pull they had in the district you see, they were farmers and - with the selling of cattle
 and all that they were - you see, they were - they really made the district what it was. You see, they had the people working }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 for them}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  and that. And - the railways were the means of transporting the stuff, such as wool and that and even the cattle - used 
to walk the cattle in, they had the cattle trains in the early Monday morning and they used to - walk them - walk the sheep or the cattle or whatever it was and send them to Newcastle to the market. You see, it was all agriculture. It made these people im
portant, farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can I ask you about the shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There wasn't any shops. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 
They were three miles away, the nearest - the big - best shops were in Annick or Verwick, that was fifteen miles each way. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 We were half way between them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you know any clergymen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Wasn't even them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There must have been a church somewhere?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
There was, the - three miles away, Kirk Newton and there was a Catholic one and a Protestant, there was a Presbyterian in Wooler. Well now each time we were - 
we were half way, Kirk Newton was west and Wooler was East as you might say. But Kirk Newton was the parish church. I can't remember the name of - what they called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you know the clergymen at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 We didn't know them, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you know any schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Just the ones where I went. Hunter they called him and he had his daughter - teaching.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you know what kind of people he spent his leisure time with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, he was just a quiet country chap. Just enjoyed the solitude of the district I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Who did the farmers associate with mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh they were among themselves. Aye. There's a one Goodson now, he's a big fellow, he's up at Kelso. He was a student at the}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4850714  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 then, now - then he got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Killum}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
 Farm, took it over when it was sold out - that's since I've been up there. And he's a great fellow up in that district. Yes, the one that - he goes to the - you know, to the hunts. With hounds and that and - any events.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What about the other employers in the district, who did they used to associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh there was just - well there was the saddler in the district and the blacksmith, they were just - they kept themselves all - within themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 They didn't spend much time with other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, they didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What sort of people would you say went to the church, Church of England I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Aye, the Church of England, well just the ordinary people - all the - anybody that was living near it and could get there. The village of Kirk Newton, the people in it would want - those that - Methodist chapel in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Mi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8590468\charrsid4850714 ll}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 field}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
, the other way on, by boss, he lived in Millfield and he used to go to it. His daughter played the organ in it. Millfield. That was the only chapel they had.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was there any difference betw
een the kind of people who went to the church and the kind of people who went to the Methodist chapel, did you notice that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well my - my - boss who was definitely Methodist and he - he - he hadn't much room for the Church of England. You know, that w
ay, just that little bit difference. Didn't make that much difference to me, I didn't bother myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Practically, oh yes, all they could, yes. Yes, all - all about the same, very little difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You can't think of any groups who were much worse off than the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There wasn't - no. There wasn't very much - all pretty well - you know, struggling along, it was really a struggle with everybody jus
t kept their head above water as you might say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you tell me something about the standard of living of any working class family that you knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well I could take - well, the platelayers, he had a - a family of - it was - I - two boys and two g
irls. Now they had a pig and they kept hens and that helped them you see, that was a big help for a family. But so we were - it was only me well it - you could get along with one but when there was four or five - they'd have some other means of bringing f
ood in well - the pigs was a big help and they - they killed he pig well then they got the bacon and that. And then they had hens, in fact, some had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 nanny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  goats and they got the goats milk. All those up at the farm, they had a cow. There's one or two hens, 
they had a cows next to it. The shepherd, he was partly paid in sheep. By the farmer, in those days, so much - oh yes. He had - he had so many flocks of sheep and they were all on the hillside. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you think that any of the working class people that you knew felt they were superior to any of the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Well - there was always some you know. The - the steward on the farm naturally he was like the foreman. He was under the farmer, he carried that, he was the fellow that was given all the order
s and - you got these fellows - different - the same as on the railway, you had the stationmaster, he was above all the rest. There was not that much in it but }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  - they were just that - they had the control of the thing the same as - you have in a factory. Did have in a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 factory}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  where you have a foreman couldn't you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 As a child did you think of some families as being respectable and some being a bit rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, there wasn't that much in - distinction in the country, no. Not - not like the town. You find that in the town I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was there a distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh aye, a craftsman - yes, there was a little bit of distinction, generally is. Oh aye. There's just that superiority with the craftsman doing the job and the other fellow working for - he's another class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your mother and father have the same attitude towards people in the different classes, did they like the lord and lady at the manor?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well they didn't see them that often - did they. Just stayed among your own people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 But did they have the same attitude towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh no, they didn't say anything against them. Just fell in line with them. In fact - in fact they looked up to them. Such as the duke of Northumberland, they were - we
ll looked up to. Still that - there's still that in Annick. But - these are nearly all gone, they're nearly all taxed out of existence. There's very few of them up there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you think that your mother thought that she belonged to the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes, just ordinary people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you think this was because she was thinking about her parents or her work or where she lived or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, just on - it's based on her own life, where she'd been - what she's been amongst all her life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was it possible at that time for people to move from one class to another and can you remember anybody doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well - you could say - you could say me mother's own brother. He started as a - a printer in the Advertiser office in Berwick. And then
 he went from there to - I think it was Ayr and then he finished up in - Leeds and Yorkshire Post, he was head overseer. He jumped up above really. Another class. Not that very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was that fairly common, did that happen fairly often?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. Not
 that very often. You didn't get that - some didn't lose their heads when they got a better position. All depends - you still see them that way yet. Some lose their heads if they get a little bit promotion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you remember anyone being described as a real lady or a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh there was plenty. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 
The - the Duke of Northumberland were really - that family was - really looked up to, the same with the Cantervilles of Sheringham Castle. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Looked up to them as - somebody you could look up to. An e
xample. There was Colonel Anderson of the Stirlings, he was fine chap. Nice family. And Lady Anderson. They - they didn't - lose their heads, they came in among everybody. Didn't matter where you met them, they would talk to you and be all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
We had the one in the village, oh aye, we knew the policeman - village policeman all right, but he was in Millfield. The next ones were in Wooler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh just ordinary. - Country bobby, just a - big canny fellows. Got along with them all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you were naughty did your mother ever say, you behave yourself or I'll call the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 It was no good, the police was too far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So you didn't have much to do with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. No, no. Not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 All right. They were just - there's very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 seldom}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  anything happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 The house you lived in at , was it rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye, we paid rent to the railway company, North Eastern Railway Company. Two and six a week. It's a lot dearer now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever see the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, no, they were - just cut off the wages, they made sure they got it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So you didn't know who your landlord was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well - the - the N.E.R. - the North Eastern Railway. It was controlled from Newcastle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What did you think about this landlord that wasn't a real person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well they were all right, you - it was really your boss. Or my father's boss I should say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you feel that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 It was a bit of a struggle, definitely, all the way through. You just had to - that's why people made for these jobs. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 The - the railways used to make them
 because their money was steady every week, they could - just a light better than being, say, at the - in the building trade where you're employed - as a job got finished well you're finished and then you're - that was the end of that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 More steady. It was a - - it was a bigger struggle for other people. Such as the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 building trade}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  as I mentioned. And - on the farm you see they were hired for the twelve month, the hands and all those were hired every - every March and they had to stay on that particular farm 
the whole year, whether they liked it or not. They were hired. It seems - it seems funny, I can never understand that. I think they've abolished it now. Used to be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 hiring}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  at Berwick and - and Annick in the first - Saturday in March each year. Then they had
 to go and - they went onto the market and the - farmers come around and made agreement with them, what their wage would be, whatever that was. Used to try to peg them down. But - they knew - as the years went on where there was good hands you know and th
ey - they could command decent wage, what - what you could call a decent wage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What did you think about the struggle that your parents had to make, did it bother you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, I - I was never really - no, no, I was fortunate that way, we never 
really had any - right hardships. I know some - I remember going to school with a lad at Milford Hill, his mother - he must have lost his father and they came from Yorkshire somewhere and she had to take a washerwoman's job on for the Grays of Millfield H
i
ll. And they had a right struggle and this poor lad - I remember I got a - I got a - I've got it there, I got a little box desk what I got for - sticking to going to school 1905 and I kept going in all weathers, you know, it was three miles there and thre
e
 miles back. And this poor lad, he fancied a desk and he got one - he got one somehow or other but - it was a right struggle for his mother. For - what Grays would pay I don't know. It wouldn't be very much. She were rent free I think. But they didn't liv
e there very long, they moved somewhere else. I just - you remember the likes of that, that was real hardship. Where the breadwinner had to - died.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 He was never ill - fortunate you know, I was very,very fortunate. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Mother and me father were - aye, we were fortunate that way. Good health. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 We wasn't - and a man goes ill all the times, in fact they fed you, the railway's help there's first class. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Makes a big difference. No, we were very fortunate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was there ever anybody in the district that you can remember who people disapproved of very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 wasn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  - no, not in our district. Not around here. It was sparsely populated you know, there was nothing, you could say up here in Newcastle. Different altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were you given lessons by either of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever have anyone coming to the house to teach you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, there wasn't anything like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
What - at Newsholme, I was five. Started at - started at Newsholme infant school then I got up to standard one when we shifted. That was 1902. We shifted to Milford and then I was in standard one again. But I knew the difference 
between the Newsholme school, the one in - it was the main school in Newsholme, knew the difference between the teaching there and I felt the difference. The teaching at the country school where the - one schoolmaster done the whole school. With all the c
lasses right through. Different altogether - you could - you get a better grip, you seem to get a grip far quicker in - in Newsholme they had a different style. It was funny. That were when I were only in standard one. And I had a standard one again at - 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Millfield}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How they number the classes then, what was the first class called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Was infants was just the - was two classes of infants. One and two and then - then standard one, two, up to seven, that was all, it was the classes in the big school. You left in standard seven, the farthest you could get. That was later date at fifteen.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What kind of lessons can you remember as being enjoyable at Newsholme?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh geography, I love it. But I hated - arithmetic.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What kind of things did you do in geography?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Well geography was just mainly the - British Empire especially, you got all the - parts of the British Empire, you can - you got that, but do - got very little of what there were beyond that. Say China and that. But we did get th
e British Empire right through. All over the British Isles you know and - what made me more interested was the railways, used to know all the railways right through all - and that's how I got keen on geography I think. You got all off be heart. Where all 
the points and places were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you just sit down and listen to the teacher talking or did you draw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 They had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 map}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
 and that. Oh - some - aye, we done a bit drawing sometimes. But it was nearly all listening, as you say, listening and taking it in. And then they'd question you on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have to learn it off by heart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You had to get it off by heart whatever it was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 And other lesson that you enjoyed besides geography?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There wasn't that much. Although there was just - 
not interested in history and that. I didn't - I could never get away with history, there's too much of the Kings and Queens, no - you know - got the Battle of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Flodden}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  and all that and all the battles of - the Scottish - I think you must have been more of 
a Scotsman our schoolmaster, he did all of Scottish battles and all the Scottish songs and he used to get - when we sing anything it was always Scottish stuff you know. Scots Wa'hae. and Wallace Blain and all these. Used to sing these at the school and ha
d
 the classes singing them. I used to get beside his - one of his sons and he - if he didn't sing well I didn't sing. He went away and he - he served his time as an engineer in Loco - British Locomotive Company at Glasgow, when I - when I left. We were bot
h the same age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Which lessons did you hate very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well I can't say that I disliked any. I just - oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Tell me something about your favourite teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well it was him, the schoolmaster was - he had a whisker in those days, aye. Like King Edward, be the same. It was - he had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Why did you think he was good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Well - it was just his outlook. He seemed to have us - he - he'd have us out for country walks sometime and you get - nature - walk, you know, he was in - he was interested in everything. This old teacher take - he'd - he'd take us for a walk. At }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Millfield}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  - at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Millfield}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  school it was, when we were living at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4850714  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
that's right. And - used to go and - you know, nature walks and that. You got a lot of - all that. That was him t
hat got the Review of Reviews, that magazine I was telling you, W.T. Stead. It was good. Well it was really his. We used to see it at the station before he got it. Was the only way you could get a hold of magazines and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you first started school what time of the day did you used to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh I had to - I could be up by seven. And get breakfast. That's when you had to have a breakfast in those days - those days 'cos there were a three mile walk. We left before eight o'clock to get there for nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you first went to school in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Newsholme}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , what time did you have to get up then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh I was all - I can't remember but it was nine o'clock start. I think we'd leave about half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 eight}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What time did you get back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh - about half past four I should think. After four, whatever time it finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So you stayed at school all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You had your dinner at school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Excepting that the new one, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 infant\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  one that they built at South Newsholme, I got home for dinner. That was just over the railway, just a few hundred yards away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you go to two schools in Newsholme?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well I - - I started at - at - at the - other one and then this infants school was built about - about six month 
after I'd started, and then it was built, I went I got past that, for standard one, had to go back to the big school again at - at Newsholme. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 
But what - that meant - carrying - meals - it wasn't very, very long I was only in standard one when we shifted, you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 And in May of 1902. I was nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What kind of a school was it a church school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh it's an ordinary country school - country - little county school it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 With boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, all mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you always walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, I - well you couldn't - there was no other means of getting there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There was - others, we'd all go together. Others in the - you know. Some came down from the farm, we all joined up. We all went together.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Just a lot of children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Aye, about - there was about a dozen of us. Boys and girls. It was hard lines on the little toddlers that were starting you know, the five year olds, I don't know how they stood it. It was three miles up there and three miles back. That was }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Millfield}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What did you have to eat for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh just sandwiches, some - or pies that your mother made. And sandwiches. That was what you carried and then you got a dinner when you got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What did you think about school did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Like it. Oh aye, I liked school all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh well they were all right. Teachers were all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did they emphasise certain things as being important in life such as manners, tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, oh aye. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Any outstanding thing that they always kept on about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Deep breathing and all that. Aye, give your lungs full. Try and make yourself as strong as you can. Play the game, oh aye. Be honest and upright and straight. Don't tell lies. Oh yes, they were good. Were good examples.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What happened when you did something the teachers disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh you got the leather belt. You got the - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 tawse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , you got that, wallop with that. Or with the hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Girls as well as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes. Both - or - if they'd done anything wrong, it wasn't very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What kind of things did you have to do to go that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well if you'd landed late in the morning for one thing. Oh well - just - I canna remember anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What about if you didn't do your work fast enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh he didn't - aye, no, he didn't - that didn't apply that way, it didn't - it - didn't lose - he could lose his temper but - I canna remember about anyone getting hit for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were your parents interested in what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh aye. As far as they could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, it wasn't necessary. It was too far away. They knew the schoolmaster well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did they ask you about what you'd been doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, oh yes. Used to tell them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 They used to meet the schoolmaster quite often did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, whenever he came - he was travelling on the train or that he'd come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did the other children in the school at Millfield come from similar homes to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh come from all over, yes, all the same, yes, came from far enough. Shepherd's sons and - from different farms all over. They all were different. There's as many came on side of Millfield as what there was on our side. All of us had a two or thre
e mile walk. Came from Lampon and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Flodden}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , that - that's the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 
Flodden}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  field what's from there and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Mitchell\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment than the others?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, there wasn't much of that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were there any gangs I - the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
No. No. No gangs. All united, we were all one big family. Yes. Aye. Well as near - it was all from different places you know, and all country - all country children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8590468\charrsid4850714 Were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  there any children who get left out of things a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Left out? I can't remember, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 After you'd got to standard seven at Millfield did you go to any other school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. There wasn't any to go to. They started to send me to - I started work then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Fifteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
I would have if I'd got the chance. I forget to tell you - we used slates in those days at that school right 'til the end. Slates and the - you know, the - very sharp p
encil. Before paper, and then we got the paper and pencils after. Towards - the last year. We were on a decimal system. Just when I left. 1908.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 That was interesting to move over to paper was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye, it was, oh it's better than the slates, when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 wipe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  your slates you wipe it all off. It was all slates before. Both at Newsholme and Millfield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Have you got any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There's no regrets, no, no. Only there wasn't enough of it, that's all. You see a big difference 
nowadays to what we had. Get yourself self educated. After when I served me time I - I had - I went in for I.C.S. - International Correspondence Schools. Was the only way you could do. You - you had to pay for that, it's still advertised you know, you - y
ou'll have seen adverts. That was when I was serving me time, went in for building construction and that. So went to them courses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How long did you get those for?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 That was until the war broke out and I had to - chuck it up. I started 1913 with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Have you done any other part time education since you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Well since I - I've - done some - went in for Esperanto a bit but - aye, bit it's - well that's just this last few years. I thought it'd be more - in use than what it is. I ca
n't understand people learning French and learning German and learning Italian where they could have the universal language.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you think you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 benefited}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  from going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh definitely. Wouldn't like it I hadn't - I wouldn't like to have been like a gipsy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have any part time jobs when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. There wasn't anything. You couldn't do any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 This is it. The first job I had was cutting thistles. Just after I left s
chool. Well you got them jobs and - and you got parks you know, they were fields and - used to let them out for cattle and that. Well my boss, I served me time, he used to buy Irish cattle, you know, bring 'em in young and then - put them onto these field
s and - fatten 'em up and then sell them, that's why he made the money. Selling this foreign cattle you see. Well I started to serve me time and - in the summer I used to take these }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 thistle}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  cutters, that was to cut the thistles you know. Scythe and that and
 you cut them, - and a sickle. Used to cut them, I got six bob a week. I was on that job for six month, that was a lovely summer. Then in October I started serving me time. Exactly sixty-two years today. Half past six, aye, funny - it was on a Wednesday, 
twenty-first of October 1908. Aye, it's funny that. And I started serving me time for four bob a week. A reduction of two bob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How did you get this first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 I got it myself,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4850714  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 
went and see me boss and - I knew him with going to school you see, and they knew the country child and hat was just a country child that's all. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Done all general work you know in the district. Prepared things and - buildings and made coffins, if there was any funerals we got the funerals. One on the second day I was there, blacksmith's wife. We had the coffin to make. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So what exactly did you do in the first year or two when you were serving your time after you'd finished cutting thistles?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 That - and that was what I was doing - just - in the way of doing repai
rs to different - sort of big houses and that and - if there was any buildings to go up - all joiner work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you do mainly repairs though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 We done all the repairs and we made new jobs if it was necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were you doing the same kind of work as the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 craftsmen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh it was what we done, oh yes, we were classed - well, really the - the boss was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 craftsman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  we were - we had two apprentices. The other apprentice was older than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 From half past six 'til five. Nine hours a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What about Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 From half past six 'til twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever work Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 The jobs was - if it was cell you once and he got a job and he called for me - so the boss give me a couple bob. I pulled him u
p, h said - I thought you got double time on Sundays. He said - he said, you're getting double time aren't you. And so I was, 'cos me wage was only four bob a week. The couple of bob for the Sunday - I said, that's only the one time. Heard of people getti
ng double time and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So you worked five and a half days a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Five and a half - that was it, aye. Fifty-three hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you get holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh just Bank Holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You didn't get a week off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I took a one. I took it, used to take it off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You didn't get any money for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Me - me boss, well he'd pay me but we always used to go away for a holiday. That year I went to Blackpool - and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you get paid when you had your holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well he - he - I was pa
id in six months, in the first six months he had to give me my money, well that was nearly three month after. Oh, he said, I'm sorry you'll have to go to work - to bank and went back and - and - I - it was six quid or something, I thought I was getting a 
lot it was all - all accumulated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So you got holidays with pay then really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh I did there, well you could call it that couldn't you. You didn't lose much of - if the last four bob did you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you think four shillings was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
It was in those days, oh yes, that was the general thing. You rose a shilling a year. I finished up with nine bob when I came out me time. Very good. Oh yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I gave the lot. It was no good. When I to
ok that six bob in at the start it was a great thing that, the first six bob off the - cutting thistles. Then I couldn't give anything until I had to wait 'til that six month then to get - bring - then I bought in pound notes. That was a big event that. I
t was a big help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you know what she spent your money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh just - anything to improve the house. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 A bit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  of furniture and that. Help things. We got better - quality things but clothes and that. But I needed them for the war and tear of me own c
lothes, with the trade, the boots and that. You shifted some leather you know with walking about. I settled there and I could settle and that made a difference. And that thing to maintain. Gas lamps were - you know, in those days - carbide gas lamps. Ther
e was no real lights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How did you get on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Champion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
, there was only - another chap and I and - a mate of mine - and the boss, we got on all right, we all worked together. Just the three of us in the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What jobs have you done since 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well since 1918 I've been all over the place.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How long did you stay as a jointer, you served your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh aye. I was there 'til 1914. I was out of me time in the - in the 1913. I was out of me time - in Oct
ober you see, the five years after and then I was - I still stayed on. 'Til the following year, the end of July. And then we came up to Newcastle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What job did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I started up here - on military huts at Backworth. That was the first job I done for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Davison\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  of Newcastle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 As a joiner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
As a joiner, oh aye, I've always - been to the trade all the time ever since. I've been a - employed as a joiner everywhere. Stuck to the trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So since 1918 you've worked as a joiner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Would you rather have had another kind of job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You enjoyed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Oh yes, it's some - nice on the bench and that. Benchwork was interesting. All depending where you were. Especially in the shipyards, all good work, first class work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes. Yes, there was - what is the A.S.W. now. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Amalgamated}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  Society of Woodworkers. Carpenters and joiners, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What was it called when you joined it first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 It was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 Carpenters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  and Joiners. Established 1860.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you take part in any of this activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Sometimes, oh yes, not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you feel that workers and employers and had the same interests or different ones?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh they - we found them having the same,
 it was necessary that, as a tradesman, you needed to work with your boss to - you see, one is as necessary as the other. One's giving the orders and another one's carrying them out. And you - there was good bosses and bad, I worked for a lot of different
 firms. Swann Hunters was the big firms in Wallsend. That was them that built the Mauritania in 1907. Oh it's always been a famous - well it's the big famous place now, it's - head of this - consortium.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you feel there were divisions of interest among workers? Some workers wanted one thing and some wanted another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh you'll get that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 everywhere}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  I think, different classes - steel trades have a different outlook to us and - we were more the finishing trades you see, where the shipwrights, they - th
ey were really it in the yards, they were laying the keel of a ship - big shipbuilding, but we were like the finishing trades like the electricians and the - joiners and that. They were - shipwrights was rally a - a fellow that was a responsible party.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What exactly did you do when you were on a ship, what things did you put in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well it was all timber work and - sometimes - and - on that Italian liner I was on, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16261249\charrsid4850714 hand railing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  and then on the class }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 de luxe rooms and you know different b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 erths and that, fixing the furniture in and - and saloons and all the general - paneling and everything, fixing the doors. Fixing the furniture in. All that class of work. Finishing off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you feel that you worked in the shipyard that there was a great division between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, the craftsman always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 held}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  himself aloof - sort of a little bit above the labourer. Definitely is because the labourer couldn't - you know, he can only do what he's told but - the craftsman, well he's responsib
le for it's turned out. Is all the difference. But there wasn't - you didn't look down on anybody, they looked - more - looked up to you as somebody responsible or - they knew that you had the full authority and you - you're fully responsible. You can put
 it that way, that some got careless. Couldn't expect them to have the same interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you think that starting work full time changed your attitude to life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, I was - I looked forward to it. It didn't change - it improved it. I looked 
forward for some time because - all the talk was about the big - the Mauritania and all that then you know. Used to look forward to be - to being on the shipyards, but I've been on both buildings and shipyards. See, about - work on cinemas and - hotels an
d all the different jobs. You'd got to a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 adapt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  yourself, there's a big difference between the building trade and the shipyards.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes, I've been at home all the time. I was fortunate that way. Lived with the old people all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you started work did it change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, no. No, they were just the same. It was an improvement really. We got well off, were - I was getting more than me father, a lot more.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 After you'd left school did you spend your Sundays any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
No, just the same. Just going around somewhere or the other - cycling away to places and that, in the summer. In the winter you just stayed home reading and that. Quiet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you take any interest in politics yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Not much. Very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Have you ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Sometimes. Took an interest. Didn't put meself out to - I was never attached to any parties or anything. I couldn't label myself as anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you take any interest in politics after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Just a - a general interest that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What were your views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well - if they were any they could be Liberal I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Why do you think you were only a bit vague, why is it not more definite, any reason particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Well just that followed Lloyd George and that, when his speeches, oh yes. When - when there was an election on. The one - I remember - one - when Sir Liddle Gray }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 came up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  north, I went to Millfield school and hea
rd him speak, now he's a great Liberal you know. And he got in for - North - for Berwick Division. He was foreign secretary when the war broke out. If you remember he declared - he was the one that had to declare the '14-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 \rquote 18 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 ar. It was the end of him real
ly. He became blind after that and - but lately - that - he made an impression in politics, me first was a Liberal but the majority of people around there were Tories, you know, they belonged a - left class is it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When was the first election that you voted in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well - it's be 1919 I think. Or was there one 1918. Aye. It was then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Who did you vote for then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Does it matter? I canna remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Were you under any pressure form your employer to vote for any particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, n
ever, never, no. Fortunately being up here, could have been if I'd been living up there. The - a lot of them voted Tory because they were - working on the streets you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever belong to a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you ever do any work for them at elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, no. Never. I should have but I never have. No, never took a keen interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way after you'd left school or did you do different things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, I just - practically the same. Yes. Cycling and walking and - I take an interest in the country and - reading a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you go out in the evenings when you first started works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, I - do you mean when I came up here. Well there wasn't much to - aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you were sixteen to eighteen years old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Aye, that was up there, oh yes, we had a - we just - usual things. And - doing bits of jobs you know, we - serving me time and - was any bits of jobs to do. There's a fellow had bees and that. Used to help him make and we made some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 beehives}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , take interest in things like that you see. Gardening and the likes of that. I used to help in that. All constructive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You didn't go out with the boys and smash lamp posts down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh no, there was nothing to smash, there was no lamps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you go to dances and things like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
No I didn't. I daresay I could have because there was barn dances and that up at the farm. But I never took - I never went to them - I - I went once to one of them, a barn dance was
 held at the farm. There was never much like that. You had to come to Newcastle if you wanted anything, that was an event.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you make any new friends in the few years after you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, just the same, just - we grew up with them all. Very little change, they were nearly all the same people all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have any special friends, any special close friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Well there was one, the stationmaster's son and I, we were great pals. He was a year older than me and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Even when you started work you were still friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Aye, he went and served his time at Wooler. And then he went up to London when he served his time as a draper and I served my time in that. I never seen him again, he went down London way. Some big - one of the big shops there. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 Gamages}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 somebody\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 . Lost him altogether. And then I got mates with the fellow I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 working}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What kind of things did you used to do, the stationmaster's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 son and}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  you when you were friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh he tried to make aeroplanes and - we had different hobbies, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You used to work together on these did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Doing things, aye. It was - we were mainly cycling and that round about and walking and that round the country here. Climbing the hills, go up to - tram
p over the hills, Syrup Hill and Cheviot. That was an event to do it you see, you always done something like that in the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your parents like this boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh yes, we got - we all got on well. Used to go to their house and all - all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When you went out did they expect you to tell them where you were going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Generally - oh they generally told them where they were going, if they're going any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 distance.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have to be back by a certain time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Generally back in by nine at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Even when you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 Aye, we'd always be back nine and ten, never any later.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How old were you when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Thirty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How long had you know your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Twelve month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Introduced by - introduced by another party. Another lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Someone you both knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 She was born in Stockton. Yes, another railway place but there you are. Her father was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 forge man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you save up money before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I'd saved a bit, oh yes, being single.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did your parents help you in setting up house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 They did in a way, yes, little bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did they give you money or things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 They give us a little bit of money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 About how long were you engaged, for about a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 About a year, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Can you tell me something about the wedding, where it was?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye, it was in Heaton. St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 Gabriel\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , aye. Early morning, aye. Boxing Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was that a Church of England church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Aye, yes. Parish church for the district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You married early in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How many guests were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh about - twenty or something like that. It was early morning. It wasn't a big event, it was, you know, 
nice and quiet. Because we both had lost our parents, one of our parents. I'd lost me mother and - she had lost her mother just - I didn't know her mother, never did know her. That's what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you get many presents from people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 We did get - oh yes, nothing outstanding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you go away for a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 We went to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 Blackpool}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 . Aye. For a week. Came back New Year's Day. Aye, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Where did you live after you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 There in Heaton. Near Heaton Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Until I - until she died. And then - got married again and I left there and - I came here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you remember the year that you left there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 '52 - 1952 - we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 left}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  there 1952, but she was dead before that. In - 1946 when she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How old was your wife when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
Aye, she was three or four years older than me. No, no, not four. About three I think. She was born 18 - 1809 - '89. That's - like that's nearly four, aye. I was '93. About four years older than me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did she have a job when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 She had - yes. She was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 milliner}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 . She worked - for one of the shops in Newcastle. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 For}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  a firm, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Had she had any jobs before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No, she had worked for them - well for different - for other firms before that I suppose, I can't remember - much to do with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did she continue working after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 No. No, she stopped it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Do you think that she enjoyed her work as a milliner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 She did, yes, in fact she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 You just had one son did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I had one son - yes. There's nothing about the second wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Was he born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Yes. In the house. Heaton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you have any medical help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Just the doctor. And a lady help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did you help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 I was there when he was born, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How soon was your wife out of bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 About a week after. Natural birth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 How did you manage while she was in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh we managed, we had to manage, I was unemployed. I was married six mont
hs and I got unemployed, I was unemployed all that winter for six months. That was a right smack. That was in 1928. Exhibition was getting built then and I thought I would have got onto it before but I didn't get on 'til two or three month before opening 
and - the next six month. I was six month married and I had six month out of work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 When was your son born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 1928. November.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What was the first job he had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Oh he started to serve his time, railroads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 As what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 As an engineer m
echanic. He's a mechanic in the - railroads at Hebburn you know. That - they're - it's all electrical work mainly. Aye, partly in - it was - what was they for used again, Reyrolls, they're }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 
linked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  up with Parsons. Railroads of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 Hebburn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , aye, big - quite a bi
g firm. He was in - electrical - in that line, aye, they specialize in a certain product you know, the switchboxes and that. In that line. He served his time there. Then - he was called up and he was in R.A.F. He served two years at the trade and he had t
o
 - he had to do two years, he had just started when his mother died. That's it, and he was seventeen when she died. Eighteen I think it was. And - she was dead as I was telling you and he - his brother was just a few days after in the November and he got 
c
alled up. I thought they could - probably would have got relief but he didn't. 'Cos the war was finished then you know, that was in 1948. So he had to go two years and he got into the R.A.F. I didn't know 'til lately the - the way he was in that R.A.F. wa
s - they were just taking so many off for the Army. Say all for the Army and he was the next one, R.A.F and lucky - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 fortunately}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
 he got into the R.A.F. which was up his street in a way. 'Cos he got in - as a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 grounds man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  and one thing and another, got quite a
n experience in the R.A.F. So he was there for his two years. And then he come back and had to complete his apprentice ship at Railroads. When he got finished he cleared off up to - started for a firm up at Berwick. Agricultural engineers. And he - that w
as where he had been - evacuated during the war and it made a big chance in him 'cos he's only ten you see and being switched up there he's - he's taken to the country. And not come back to the town for anything, he's over at Wooler now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 So what was his job with this firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Engineer - he's still in - aye, well, an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 agricultural}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  engineer, he adapted himself to that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 Did he continue in that same line?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 He - he - he continued ad then he went in taxis for - he had a taxi and he - had d
one that for - but that was only like a sideline. And then - he got on for this - Castrol Company and he's - on - doing - for maintenance work for them to have in the district, all around the borders. He's on there now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1719500 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 What kind of things does he do?
