My first wife, Adelaide "Young" was born in Stockton, County Durham in 1839 they moved to Sunderland where she went to school and I understood her siste
r 10 years older had to take money each day to pay for her schooling (coppers in those days) after they removed to Newcastle where she served her apprenticeship as milliner which she followed right up to 1927 when she and I got married. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 (6 months after I b
ecame unemployed all that winter 1928-9 along with other three millions our income was, unemployed benefit for husband and wife 23/- and child 3/- per week, then they applied after a while what was known as the gap, (or benefit stop) through the USA deman
ding their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8603738 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 80m., the brokers making a million in the deal). My wife never took up }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 millinery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  work having been fully occupied at home with our son born 1928 and her old father Jack Young who died 1940 at the ripe age of 91 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 He was born in Sunderland in 1848, his father also steel }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 forge man}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714  was born in Gateshead 1809, when this country was becoming }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 industrialized}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 , wood being replaced with steel and now in 1970 its all steel and concrete.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 My first wife's father having followed his dad as a steel }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 forge man}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
 all his life, one job he was proud of was when he helped to Forge the Stern Frame of the famous Passenger Liner the "Mauritania" built in Swan and Hunters Wallsend Shipyard, which held the Worlds Speed Record for many years between the British
 Isles and America.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 
After the Second World War my first wife took ill and died in 1946 and a fortnight after our sons 18th birthday made him eligible for two years in the forces and was called up right away (this was abolished a few years later) he h
aving to break his apprenticeship as Electric Engineer with Beyralls, Hebburn and was taken into the Air Force which was what he fancied, he told me after it was just luck, as the chap in the row next to him was the last required for the Army and he start
ed the new numbers for the R.A.F. 'probably if he had asked go in the R.A.F. they would have dumped him in the Army'.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5985306 AA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid411975\charrsid4850714 My second wife Lily }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9769733\charrsid4850714 Emmeline}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
